<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(p) Persons who export used, recycled or reclaimed controlled 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
substances must label their bill of lading or invoice indicating 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
that the controlled substance is used, recycled or reclaimed. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(q) Persons who import heels of controlled substances must 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
label their bill of lading or invoice indicating that the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
controlled substance in the container is a heel. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(r) Every person who brings back a container with a heel to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the United States must report the annual quantity brought back 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
into the United States within 45 days of the end of the control 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
period. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(s) Every person who imports or exports used, recycled or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
reclaimed group II, class I controlled substances, or class II 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
controlled substances must report its annual level within 45 days 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of the end of the control period. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(t) Every person who transships a controlled substance must 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
maintain records that indicate that the controlled substance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shipment originated in one country destined for another country, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and does not enter interstate commerce with the United States. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(u) Any person who submits an order to a producer or importer 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for a controlled substance for an essential use must report the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
annual quantity received from each producer or importer within 45 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
days of the end of the control period. Those persons receiving 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
controlled substances under the exemption for laboratories must 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
provide a detailed description of the analytical procedures for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
which the specific controlled substance is essential and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
reference the published instructions, standards or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
specifications. The person reporting should submit the following: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The identity and address of the person; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The name, quantity, and level of controlled substance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
transformed or the name, quantity and volume destroyed; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) A copy of the invoice or receipt documenting the sale of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the controlled substance to the person; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) A certification that production allowances were expended 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for the production of the controlled substance; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) If the controlled substance is transformed, the name, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
quantity, and verification of the commercial use of the resulting 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
chemical transformed; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) If the controlled substance is destroyed, the efficiency 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of the destruction process. 
